<figureCitation box="[413,558,575,600]" captionStart="FIGURES 106–126" captionStartId="46.[151,264,1788,1813]" captionTargetBox="[204,1383,168,1769]" captionTargetId="figure@46.[204,1383,166,1769]" captionTargetPageId="46" captionText="FIGURES 106–126. Drasteria specimens. 106–111. D. caucasica (Kolenati, 1848), Bishkek environs, Kyrgyzstan (106, 107), Usek valley, Dzhungar Ala-Too, Kazakhstan (phenotype hyblaeoides) (108), Uch-Turfan, Kashgaria, China (phenotype hyblaeoides) (109, 110), Usek valley, Dzhungar Alatau Mts., Kazakhstan (111). 112–114: Drasteria caucasica astrida (Eversmann, 1857), lectotype (112: upperside; 113: underside; 114: labels). 115–117. D. hyblaeoides (Moore, 1878), holotype, upperside (115), underside (116), labels (117). 118–120. D. cashmirensis (Hampson, 1894), holotype (118: upperside; 119: labels), Naltar, Pakistan (120). 121–123. D. saisani saisani (Staudinger, 1882), lectotype (121: upperside, 122: underside; 123: labels). 124–126. D. saisani clara (Staudinger, 1894), lectotype (124: upperside; 125: underside; 126: labels)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3451766" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3451766/files/figure.png" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">Figs. 115, 116</figureCitation>
) in ZSI (Sheela 
<emphasis box="[726,771,576,600]" italics="true" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">et al</emphasis>
.: 2019: 306), labelled: “TYPE” (white paper, printed by red ink); “422/2” (handwritten, white paper); “422” (printed, white paper); “[H]eliothis | [h]yblaeoides | Type Moore” (white paper, handwritten). The type specimen condition is very bad, antennae, almost all legs, abdomen absent.
</paragraph>
